reviewText: My husband loves "Maximum Overdrive" so when I saw the chance to buy it along with another movie-as a combo pack- I jumped on it. Who doesn't like a two-fer? I'll do most anything to feel as if I'm getting a good deal! We haven't watched "Raw Deal" yet, but as I knew we would-we loved "Maximum Overdrive".

reviewText: This is a good deal here folks.  Two great films for one low price.  Maximum Overdrive is pretty hard to find on it's own so the extra feature (Raw Deal) is pretty much just a bonus for me.  Not a huge fan of Raw Deal.  I mean, don't get me wrong.  It has tons of cheese value, as does Maximum Overdrive, but it just doesn't hold the same nostalgic charm that most action films I watched as a kid.The picture quality looks outstanding on my 32' Sceptre LCD flat screen, with my Magnavox blu ray player using the 1080i upconversion feature & the sound is amazing.  Both films are presented in 16 x 9 widescreen, with 5.1 Surround.  Sadly, there are no special features to speak of, but I kinda figured that given the price.

reviewText: Anyone who watched movies in the eighties, have probably seen both of these films.  One a outlandish horror movie about what would happen if our electronics came to life.  The other is just a typical Arnie action movie, both definately worth a watch.
summary: a must for eighties movie fans.
